It could be 2 things:

1. You may have not waited for the audio to load.
2. You have not paused and reset the audio.

Here is how fix it:

```
//at the start of your script
var audio = new Audio(&quot;audiosrc.mp3&quot;);
var loadStatus = 0;
$( window ).on( &quot;load&quot;, function() {
setTimeout(function(){loadStatus=1}, 2000);
})
function playAudio() {
   if (loadStatus === 1) {//check page wasn’t just loaded
   //make sure audio is reset
   audio.pause();
   audio.currentTime = 0;
   //play
   audio.play();
   }
}
```
Also, safari does not let you run sound when it has not been initialised by a user event. See [this question](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26205767/sound-wont-play-if-invoked-on-ajax-success-function)

